This paper deals with LDPC codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory community (cs.IT). The paper also discusses graph properties and algorithms for constructing LDPC codes, which are relevant to the field of graph theory (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of edge coloring, which is a common technique in graph theory and combinatorics (cs.FM). The paper also discusses the use of QC-LDPC codes, which are commonly used in communication networks (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the removal of trapping sets, which is a common problem in coding theory and optimization (cs.SI).
